OMIAL 
The vast majority of differential equations can’t be solved, so in these cases we resort 
to numerical methods, that will allow us to approximate solutions to differential 
equations .This paper treats algorithms of numerical methods for ordinary and 
partial differential equations, complexity of methods, speed of convergence, number 
of iterations needed and methods for finding all simple zeros of polynomials 
simultaneously. 
